<item>
            <title>[PAY-4064] Preprod - ACH refund on an eligible transaction returns 500 instead of processing the refund</title>
                <link>https://wellfit.atlassian.net/browse/PAY-4064</link>
                <project id="10016" key="PAY">Payments</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Environment:&lt;/b&gt; Sbox (preprod)&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Component:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;tt&gt;payment-management-api&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Endpoint:&lt;/b&gt; {{POST /api/transactions/&lt;/p&gt;
{transactionId}
&lt;p&gt;/refund}}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Description:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When submitting a valid, eligible ACH refund (partial or full) against a settled transaction, the endpoint returns HTTP 500 and does not process the refund. All &lt;em&gt;negative&lt;/em&gt; validation paths for the same transaction behave correctly and return their expected client errors &#8212; the failure is isolated to the happy path where the refund is actually eligible and should be executed. This points to a defect in the refund execution/processing logic downstream of the eligibility and validation checks, rather than in request handling, auth, or validation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Preconditions:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Valid bearer token with &lt;tt&gt;WellfitPaymentsAPI.RefundPayments&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;WellfitPaymentManagementAPI.Full&lt;/tt&gt; scopes.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A settled ACH transaction that is eligible for refund  (Approved with TransactionStatusiD = 6 ) exists (e.g. &lt;tt&gt;transactionId = 01KQZQSEZ2PFKTRNKTSD44ETJN&lt;/tt&gt;).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Refund amount is within the original transaction amount and inside the valid refund window.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
</description>
